good game is good

tldr;
play

Such a gr8 modern MOBA game for playin with friends. and If you wanna be a grate dota player, you have Looooooooong way to go.;
Sometimes you can get bored by toxic community players. but every free or cheap games have this issues right?

I passed over Four years but still so much to learn here.

You will die a lot but it will feel really good at the end;
Amazing boss fights;
Perfect level design with lots of impressive conections between areas;
Lots of weapon variety;
No "hand-helding";
Really immersive athmosphere;
lots of secrets.

Man, it does have it all.

Pros:
- Souls game;

Cons:
- Some reused bosses;

P.S.: I have and played the original Dark Souls 2, but the version Scholar of the First Sin includes some improvements.

Q: You clocked in 100+ hrs in a game you don't like, why?
A: Achievements.

The pros:
- Turn-based instead of cancerous RTwP;
- Co-op;
- Good voice acting;
- Decent visuals for cRPG. 

Now, the cons:
- Almost non-existent plot with rocky pacing (final part was done in a hurry because devs were running out of money and it shows);
- Extremely forgettable characters;
- Custom character has no content so you're stuck with playing as an Origin character If you don't want to feel like your MC is out of place;
- Balance still sux in some cases, even with all the fixes of Definitive Edition there are still weird difficulty spikes;
- No roleplaying since you are required to go murderhobo because of XP. If your map isn't covered in bodies at the end of each Act you'll in for a bad time because of aforementioned balance issues; 
- Awful inventory management;
- On top of that, Diablo loot system which means you have to be buried in your inventory 24/7;
- No sense of progression other than numerical (diablo loot system strikes again) since you're too dependent on your armour, rather than skills;
- Main feature (elemental and other surfaces) goes from nice mechanic to overbearing shtick really fast;
- Despite 'go anywhere' narrative the game is pretty linear since every map is divided into areas with a corresponding level attached to them, so little to none variety in quest order. Playthroughs will be the same (unless you cheese, which isn't my cup of tea).

All in all, subpar experience. Wouldn't recommend unless you desperately need an RPG for co-op.
